data.name: ResultOption_Description
data.value: Adds a single contest result to the results file. A result must be in the form: "<CONTESTANT-1> <SCORE-1>, <CONTESTANT-2> <SCORE-2>". Replace <CONTESTANT-n> with the contestants' names such as, Team One, Team Two, etc. Names cannot start with - or --, and they cannot include the {0} symbol. Scores must be non-negative, whole numbers without any separator symbols, which means for example that 1000 is appropriate but 1,000 is not. Example: rankings -r "My Team 1{0} Other Team 0"

data.name: ResultOption_Validation_MissingContestantResultSeparator
data.value: A result must be separated into two parts by the {0} symbol; one part for each contestant's name and score.

data.name: ResultOption_Validation_MultipleContestantResultSeparators
data.value: A result can only contain one {0} symbol.

data.name: EmptyOrWhiteSpace
data.value: Value cannot be empty or white-space.

data.name: CannotContainNewLine
data.value: Value cannot contain a new line.

data.name: ResultOption_Validation_NewLineWithinContestantResult
data.value: A result must not contain any line breaks, it must be a single line.

data.name: ResultOption_Validation_NoContestantResult
data.value: A result must include the results for both contestants. Cannot find a result for contestant {0}.

data.name: ResultOption_Validation_NoContestantName
data.value: A result must include names for both contestants. Cannot find a name for contestant {0}.

data.name: ResultOption_Validation_NoContestantScore
data.value: A result must include scores for both contestants. Cannot find a score for contestant {0}.

data.name: FileOption_Description
data.value: Imports a set of results from the specified file into the results file. Eeach result must be in the form: "<CONTESTANT-1> <SCORE-1>, <CONTESTANT-2> <SCORE-2>". See help for the --result option for further information.

data.name: FileOption_Validation_FileDoesNotExist
data.value: The file specified does not exist.
